{{about|institutional residencies|the album by Jason Moran|Artist in Residence (album)}}
'''Artist-in-residence programs''' exist to invite [[artist]]s, academicians, curators, to reside within the premises of an institution.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-14386970|title=What do artists-in-residence do?|first=Rebecca|last=Cafe|date=4 August 2011|publisher=|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>

Some residency programs are incorporated within larger institutions, such as museums, universities, or galleries. Other organizations exist solely to support residential exchange programs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nps.gov/subjects/arts/air.htm|title=Be an Artist-in-Residence - Arts in the Parks (U.S. National Park Service)|website=www.nps.gov}}</ref>

Various '''Composer-in-Residence''' programs exist, for example with orchestras and with universities.<ref>{{cite web|title=American Composers Alliance|url=https://composers.com/loretta-jankowski|publisher=American Composers Alliance}}</ref>

