{{Culture of Bangladesh}} '''Barsha Utsab''' ({{lang-bn|বর্ষা উৎসব}} ''Barṣā uṯsaba'') also known an '''Barsha Mangal Utsab''' is a day-long [[Monsoon]] salutation festival celebrated in [[Bangladesh]]. The festival date is set according to the lunisolar [[Bengali calendar]] as the first day of its third month ''[[Asharh]]'', usually falls on 13 June of the [[Gregorian Calendar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bdnews24.com/media-en/2016/07/22/barsha-festival|title=Barsha festival|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2015/jun/13/monsoon-festival-celebrated-capital-calls-rain-water-conservation|title=Monsoon festival celebrated in capital, calls for rain water conservation - Dhaka Tribune|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/108379/%E2%80%98Monsoon-Festival%E2%80%99-held-in-city|title=‘Monsoon Festival’ held in city|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref>This day is marked with colourful celebration included singing performances, drama, poetry recitation, screening of cinemas on rain, puppet show, [[Hilsha]] Fest and many other programmes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/lifestyle/14760-come-rain-or-shine-monsoon-festivals-around-asia.html|title=Come rain or shine: Monsoon festivals around Asia|first=The Myanmar|last=Times|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newstoday.com.bd/index.php?option=details&news_id=2444961&date=2016-06-16|title='Barsha Festival' held in city|first=Hafez Ahmed @|last=http://www.newstoday.com.bd|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref> Traditionally women wear sky blue saris to celebrate the first day of [[Wet season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/event/monsoon-sets-rhythm-97558|title=Monsoon sets in rhythm|date=16 June 2015|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/post/47836|title=Udichi Shilpigosthi celebrates first day of monsoon|first=The|last=Independent|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://print.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/old/2007/06/15/1170.html|title=Barsha Utsab at Charukala today|first=Hafez Ahmed at|last=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com|publisher=|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref>
